CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1959, page A1, reads: "DBR's Legal Staff - Prothonotary David B. Roberts (center) confers with his solicitor, Ralph Smith (left) and assistant solicitor, George W. Shields (right) on one of the many knotty legal issues which reach the prothonotary's office. After four months of diligent work, Attorney Shields has won unstinted commendation from Mr. Roberts and Solicitor Smith. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Solicitor Ralph Smith, Prothonotary David B. Roberts, and Atty. George W. Shields, posed in Roberts's office with images and documents hung on wall
